---
layout: tool.njk
category: After Effects
title: AE Installer
description: Windows app for installing After Effects scripts, ScriptUI panels, plugins, and CEP extensions — without manually navigating program folders. Auto-detects installed AE versions, supports drag-and-drop, and puts files exactly where AE expects them.
version: v1.0.0
platform: Windows · After Effects 2020+
---
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Download and unzip</li>
    <li>Run <strong>AE Installer.exe</strong> &mdash; no install required</li>
    <li>Optional: run <code>create_shortcuts.bat</code> to add a Desktop and Start Menu shortcut</li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Features</summary>
  <ul class="tool-shortcuts">
    <li><strong>Auto-detects AE versions</strong> Scans your system and lists every After Effects install</li>
    <li><strong>Correct destination</strong> Scripts, ScriptUI Panels, Plug-ins, and CEP extensions each go to the right folder automatically</li>
    <li><strong>Drag &amp; drop</strong> Drop files directly onto the app or use the file browser</li>
    <li><strong>ZXP / CEP extensions</strong> Extracts zip-packaged extensions to the user-level CEP extensions folder (no admin required)</li>
    <li><strong>Overwrite control</strong> Prompts before replacing existing files &mdash; Yes, Yes to All, No (skip), or Cancel (abort)</li>
    <li><strong>UAC elevation</strong> Detects when admin rights are needed and offers to relaunch elevated</li>
    <li><strong>Standalone exe</strong> Single file, no Python or dependencies required</li>
  </ul>
</details>
